{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-novel-version-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon; Novel Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-08",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/themaltesefalconnovel_2603_librivox/maltesefalcon_08_hammett_128kb.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "Horse Feathers",
  "reader_name": "NLizer",
  "page_num": 2,
  "page_total": 4,
  "page_start_sec": 244.128,
  "page_end_sec": 511.94,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.588,
  "corrected": "claude",
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 244.128,
      "end": 246.14,
      "text": "Brigid O'Shaughnessy jumped out of the armchair",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 246.24,
      "end": 246.44,
      "text": "crying,"
    },
    {
      "start": 247.14,
      "end": 248.8,
      "text": "\"Why don't you make him tell the truth?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 249.32,
      "end": 250.84,
      "text": "and slapped Cairo on the cheek."
    },
    {
      "start": 251.552,
      "end": 252.69,
      "text": "Cairo yelled inarticulately.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 254.176,
      "end": 256.74,
      "text": "Dundy pushed the girl back into the chair with",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 256.74,
      "end": 259.2,
      "text": "the hand that was not holding the Levantine's arm"
    },
    {
      "start": 259.32,
      "end": 260.08,
      "text": "and growled:"
    },
    {
      "start": 260.7,
      "end": 261.34,
      "text": "\"None of that now.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 261.68,
      "end": 261.78,
      "text": "Spade,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 262.58,
      "end": 263.4,
      "text": "lighting his cigarette,"
    },
    {
      "start": 263.58,
      "end": 264.68,
      "text": "grinned softly through smoke"
    },
    {
      "start": 265.04,
      "end": 265.9,
      "text": "and told Tom:"
    },
    {
      "start": 266.08,
      "end": 267.54,
      "text": "\"She's impulsive.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 267.96,
      "end": 268.76,
      "text": "\"Yeah,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 269.14,
      "end": 269.96,
      "text": "Tom agreed."
    },
    {
      "start": 271.264,
      "end": 273.1,
      "text": "Dundy scowled down at the girl and asked:",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 273.4,
      "end": 275.26,
      "text": "\"What do you want us to think the truth is?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 276.42,
      "end": 277.28,
      "text": "\"Not what he said,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 277.5,
      "end": 277.96,
      "text": "she replied."
    },
    {
      "start": 278.26,
      "end": 279.7,
      "text": "\"Not anything he said.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 280.68,
      "end": 281.6,
      "text": "She turned to Spade."
    },
    {
      "start": 281.88,
      "end": 282.7,
      "text": "\"Is it?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 283.86,
      "end": 284.6,
      "text": "\"How do I know?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 284.86,
      "end": 285.76,
      "text": "Spade responded."
    },
    {
      "start": 286.16,
      "end": 288.26,
      "text": "\"I was out in the kitchen mixing an"
    },
    {
      "start": 288.4,
      "end": 289.9,
      "text": "omelette when it all happened,"
    },
    {
      "start": 290.02,
      "end": 290.52,
      "text": "wasn't I?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 291.36,
      "end": 292.34,
      "text": "She wrinkled her forehead,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 292.48,
      "end": 293.88,
      "text": "studying him with eyes that"
    },
    {
      "start": 294.24,
      "end": 295.36,
      "text": "perplexity clouded."
    },
    {
      "start": 295.4,
      "end": 297.42,
      "text": "Tom grunted in disgust.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 297.6,
      "end": 297.7,
      "text": "Dundy,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 298.52,
      "end": 299.72,
      "text": "still scowling at the girl,"
    },
    {
      "start": 299.78,
      "end": 300.78,
      "text": "ignored Spade's speech"
    },
    {
      "start": 300.78,
      "end": 301.4,
      "text": "and asked her:"
    },
    {
      "start": 301.42,
      "end": 303.24,
      "text": "\"If he's not telling the truth,"
    },
    {
      "start": 305.56,
      "end": 306.2,
      "text": "and not you?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 306.72,
      "end": 307.2,
      "text": "\"Oh,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 307.32,
      "end": 309.26,
      "text": "he was frightened to death when I struck him,"
    },
    {
      "start": 309.34,
      "end": 309.8,
      "text": "she replied,"
    },
    {
      "start": 310.14,
      "end": 312.36,
      "text": "looking contemptuously at the"
    },
    {
      "start": 312.4,
      "end": 312.96,
      "text": "Levantine."
    },
    {
      "start": 313.22,
      "end": 316.18,
      "text": "Cairo's face flushed where it was not blood-smeared."
    },
    {
      "start": 316.56,
      "end": 317.26,
      "text": "He exclaimed:"
    },
    {
      "start": 317.42,
      "end": 318.12,
      "text": "\"Pfoo!"
    },
    {
      "start": 318.26,
      "end": 319.12,
      "text": "Another lie!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 319.79,
      "end": 321.08,
      "text": "She kicked his leg,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 321.28,
      "end": 324.22,
      "text": "the high heel of her blue slipper striking him just below the knee."
    },
    {
      "start": 325.152,
      "end": 326.62,
      "text": "Dundy pulled him away from her while"
    },
    {
      "start": 326.62,
      "end": 328.46,
      "text": "big Tom came to stand close to her,"
    },
    {
      "start": 328.5,
      "end": 328.84,
      "text": "rumbling:"
    },
    {
      "start": 329.36,
      "end": 329.96,
      "text": "\"Behave,"
    },
    {
      "start": 329.96,
      "end": 330.24,
      "text": "sister."
    },
    {
      "start": 330.52,
      "end": 332.14,
      "text": "That's no way to act.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 332.86,
      "end": 334.0,
      "text": "\"Then make him tell the truth,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 334.2,
      "end": 335.18,
      "text": "she said defiantly."
    },
    {
      "start": 336.18,
      "end": 337.06,
      "text": "\"We'll do that all right,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 337.16,
      "end": 337.64,
      "text": "he promised."
    },
    {
      "start": 337.84,
      "end": 338.9,
      "text": "\"Just don't get rough.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 339.96,
      "end": 340.46,
      "text": "Dundy,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 340.52,
      "end": 343.52,
      "text": "looking at Spade with green eyes hard and bright and satisfied,"
    },
    {
      "start": 343.8,
      "end": 345.08,
      "text": "addressed his subordinate:"
    },
    {
      "start": 345.24,
      "end": 345.376,
      "text": "\"Well,"
    },
    {
      "start": 346.16,
      "end": 346.44,
      "text": "Tom,"
    },
    {
      "start": 346.64,
      "end": 349.48,
      "text": "I don't guess we'll go wrong pulling the lot of them in.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 350.66,
      "end": 351.84,
      "text": "Tom nodded gloomily.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 352.8,
      "end": 355.4,
      "text": "Spade left the door and advanced to the center of the room,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 355.904,
      "end": 358.94,
      "text": "dropping his cigarette into a tray on the table as he passed it."
    },
    {
      "start": 359.78,
      "end": 361.78,
      "text": "His smile and manner were amiably composed."
    },
    {
      "start": 362.74,
      "end": 363.44,
      "text": "\"Don't be in a hurry,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 363.52,
      "end": 363.9,
      "text": "he said."
    },
    {
      "start": 364.416,
      "end": 365.64,
      "text": "Everything can be explained.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 366.9,
      "end": 367.46,
      "text": "\"I bet you,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 367.62,
      "end": 368.5,
      "text": "Dundy agreed,"
    },
    {
      "start": 368.74,
      "end": 369.2,
      "text": "sneering."
    },
    {
      "start": 370.272,
      "end": 371.3,
      "text": "Spade bowed to the girl.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 371.48,
      "end": 372.76,
      "text": "\"Miss O'Shaughnessy,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 372.86,
      "end": 373.3,
      "text": "he said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 373.8,
      "end": 376.98,
      "text": "may I present Lieutenant Dundy and Detective-sergeant Polhaus.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 377.48,
      "end": 378.8,
      "text": "He bowed to Dundy."
    },
    {
      "start": 379.58,
      "end": 381.9,
      "text": "\"Miss O'Shaughnessy is an operative in my employ.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 383.04,
      "end": 384.84,
      "text": "Joel Cairo said indignantly:",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 384.82,
      "end": 386.04,
      "text": "\"That isn't so."
    },
    {
      "start": 386.28,
      "end": 386.82,
      "text": "She—\""
    },
    {
      "start": 387.17,
      "end": 390.12,
      "text": "Spade interrupted him in a quite loud, but still",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 390.22,
      "end": 390.88,
      "text": "genial, voice:"
    },
    {
      "start": 391.22,
      "end": 392.94,
      "text": "\"I hired her just recently,"
    },
    {
      "start": 393.12,
      "end": 393.64,
      "text": "yesterday."
    },
    {
      "start": 394.7,
      "end": 395.12,
      "text": "This is Mr."
    },
    {
      "start": 395.26,
      "end": 395.84,
      "text": "Joel Cairo,"
    },
    {
      "start": 396.08,
      "end": 396.56,
      "text": "a friend—"
    },
    {
      "start": 396.8,
      "end": 397.82,
      "text": "an acquaintance,"
    },
    {
      "start": 397.94,
      "end": 398.44,
      "text": "at any rate—"
    },
    {
      "start": 398.54,
      "end": 399.03,
      "text": "of Thursby's."
    },
    {
      "start": 399.36,
      "end": 402.5,
      "text": "He came to me this afternoon and tried to hire me to find something"
    },
    {
      "start": 402.64,
      "end": 405.52,
      "text": "Thursby was supposed to have on him when he was bumped off."
    },
    {
      "start": 406.28,
      "end": 406.9,
      "text": "It looked funny,"
    },
    {
      "start": 407.04,
      "end": 407.94,
      "text": "the way he put it to"
    },
    {
      "start": 407.94,
      "end": 408.12,
      "text": "me,"
    },
    {
      "start": 408.56,
      "end": 409.44,
      "text": "so I wouldn't touch it."
    },
    {
      "start": 409.84,
      "end": 410.96,
      "text": "Then he pulled a gun—"
    },
    {
      "start": 411.18,
      "end": 412.94,
      "text": "well, never mind that unless"
    },
    {
      "start": 412.94,
      "end": 413.14,
      "text": "never mind that,"
    },
    {
      "start": 413.14,
      "end": 413.32,
      "text": "it comes to a point"
    },
    {
      "start": 413.88,
      "end": 415.92,
      "text": "of laying charges against each other."
    },
    {
      "start": 416.26,
      "end": 416.86,
      "text": "Anyway,"
    },
    {
      "start": 417.1,
      "end": 419.38,
      "text": "after talking it over with Miss O'Shaughnessy,"
    },
    {
      "start": 419.78,
      "end": 421.46,
      "text": "I thought maybe I could get something out"
    },
    {
      "start": 421.46,
      "end": 423.84,
      "text": "of him about Miles's and Thursby's killings,"
    },
    {
      "start": 424.16,
      "end": 425.52,
      "text": "so I asked him to come up here."
    },
    {
      "start": 426.6,
      "end": 428.72,
      "text": "Maybe we put the questions to him a little rough,"
    },
    {
      "start": 429.12,
      "end": 430.12,
      "text": "but he wasn't hurt any,"
    },
    {
      "start": 430.66,
      "end": 432.36,
      "text": "not enough to have to cry for help."
    },
    {
      "start": 433.24,
      "end": 434.56,
      "text": "I'd already had to take his gun"
    },
    {
      "start": 434.56,
      "end": 435.66,
      "text": "away from him again.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 437.12,
      "end": 437.86,
      "text": "As Spade talked",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 438.08,
      "end": 440.12,
      "text": "anxiety came into Cairo's reddened face."
    },
    {
      "start": 440.88,
      "end": 441.5,
      "text": "His eyes moved"
    },
    {
      "start": 441.56,
      "end": 442.54,
      "text": "jerkily up and down,"
    },
    {
      "start": 442.64,
      "end": 444.38,
      "text": "shifting their focus uneasily between"
    },
    {
      "start": 444.38,
      "end": 446.2,
      "text": "the floor and Spade's bland face."
    },
    {
      "start": 447.2,
      "end": 449.3,
      "text": "Dundy confronted Cairo and bruskly demanded:",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 449.56,
      "end": 450.04,
      "text": "\"Well,"
    },
    {
      "start": 450.26,
      "end": 451.64,
      "text": "what've you got to say to that?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 452.736,
      "end": 454.8,
      "text": "Cairo had nothing to say for nearly a minute",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 454.8,
      "end": 457.04,
      "text": "while he stared at the Lieutenant's chest."
    },
    {
      "start": 457.76,
      "end": 458.88,
      "text": "When he lifted his eyes,"
    },
    {
      "start": 458.92,
      "end": 459.9,
      "text": "they were shy and wary."
    },
    {
      "start": 460.58,
      "end": 462.04,
      "text": "\"I don't know what I should say,\""
    },
    {
      "start": 462.14,
      "end": 462.66,
      "text": "he murmured."
    },
    {
      "start": 463.16,
      "end": 464.74,
      "text": "His embarrassment seemed genuine."
    },
    {
      "start": 465.86,
      "end": 466.8,
      "text": "\"Try telling the facts,\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 467.08,
      "end": 467.9,
      "text": "Dundy suggested."
    },
    {
      "start": 468.96,
      "end": 469.4,
      "text": "\"The facts?\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 470.24,
      "end": 471.44,
      "text": "Cairo's eyes fidgeted,"
    },
    {
      "start": 471.68,
      "end": 473.9,
      "text": "though their gaze did not actually leave the Lieutenant's."
    },
    {
      "start": 474.8,
      "end": 477.48,
      "text": "\"What assurance have I that the facts will be believed?\""
    },
    {
      "start": 478.72,
      "end": 479.64,
      "text": "\"Quit stalling.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 479.76,
      "end": 482.42,
      "text": "All you've got to do is swear to a complaint that"
    },
    {
      "start": 482.42,
      "end": 485.18,
      "text": "they took a poke at you and the warrant-clerk will"
    },
    {
      "start": 485.18,
      "end": 487.58,
      "text": "believe you enough to issue a warrant that'll"
    },
    {
      "start": 487.56,
      "end": 488.76,
      "text": "let us throw them in the can.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 489.76,
      "end": 491.56,
      "text": "Spade spoke in an amused tone:",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 492.08,
      "end": 494.86,
      "text": "\"Go ahead, Cairo. Make him happy. Tell him"
    },
    {
      "start": 494.88,
      "end": 497.38,
      "text": "you'll do it, and then we'll swear to one against"
    },
    {
      "start": 497.32,
      "end": 499.52,
      "text": "you, and he'll have the lot of us.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 500.38,
      "end": 501.1,
      "text": "Cairo cleared",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 501.1,
      "end": 503.42,
      "text": "his throat and looked nervously around the room"
    },
    {
      "start": 503.54,
      "end": 505.4,
      "text": "not into the eyes of anyone there."
    },
    {
      "start": 506.38,
      "end": 506.92,
      "text": "Dundy blew",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 506.92,
      "end": 509.3,
      "text": "breath through his nose in a puff that was not"
    },
    {
      "start": 509.48,
      "end": 510.5,
      "text": "quite a snort and said:"
    },
    {
      "start": 510.64,
      "end": 511.94,
      "text": "\"Get your hats.\""
    }
  ]
}